Candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the last presidential election, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar has enjoined the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) to ensure free and fair elections in Saturday’s governorship elections in Kogi and Bayelsa States.
Atiku in a statement by his media office, advised electorate in the two states to vote wisely by electing capable hands to steer the affairs of their states.
He told them to take serious interest in the choices they make as they cast their votes, and urged PDP members to use the power of their overwhelming strength in those two states in ensuring that its flag remains standing in the Bayelsa State Government House.
According to him, the people of Kogi State should “begin to have a feel of better life under a PDP administration.”
He reminded the voters that the senatorial election in Kogi West is equally crucial, and said they should to turn out in their numbers to defend the seat.
The former Vice President told the people that the leadership of the  PDP has abiding confidence in the voters in Kogi West senatorial election, adding that “the choices before them is between a continuation of quality representation at the Senate and a promise of meaningless change.”
Atiku also called  on all political actors to exhibit necessary decorum and sportsmanship.